@newbie4444
Before you take a new loan, make sure you have enough money in your bank to pay the loan in the event you lose your job. It is also your responsibility to make sure you have an insurance policy to cover any unforeseen circumstances.
Now, can the bank charge you more if they are making losses? Should you pay more interest if you suddenly earn more? No. it is an agreement between 2 parties and whatever happens in between doesn't void or change the agreement to benefit either sides. Period

